{"id": "EUVD-2024-0947", "enisaUuid": "c8a2243c-e93c-3521-96c3-9ae2f4868a5b", "description": "Cilium is a networking, observability, and security solution with an eBPF-based dataplane. Prior to versions 1.13.13, 1.14.8, and 1.15.2, in Cilium clusters with IPsec enabled and traffic matching Layer 7 policies, IPsec-eligible traffic between a node's Envoy proxy and pods on other nodes is sent unencrypted and IPsec-eligible traffic between a node's DNS proxy and pods on other nodes is sent unencrypted. This issue has been resolved in Cilium 1.15.2, 1.14.8, and 1.13.13. There is no known workaround for this issue.", "datePublished": "2024-03-18T21:36:10", "dateUpdated": "2024-08-02T00:48:49", "baseScore": 6.1, "baseScoreVersion": "3.1", "baseScoreVector": "CVSS:3.1/AV:A/AC:H/PR:N/UI:N/S:C/C:H/I:N/A:N", "references": ["https://github.com/cilium/cilium/security/advisories/GHSA-j89h-qrvr-xc36", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2024-28249", "https://github.com/cilium/cilium", "https://github.com/cilium/cilium/releases/tag/v1.13.13", "https://github.com/cilium/cilium/releases/tag/v1.14.8", "https://github.com/cilium/cilium/releases/tag/v1.15.2"], "aliases": ["CVE-2024-28249", "GHSA-j89h-qrvr-xc36"], "assigner": "GitHub_M", "epss": 0.2, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "2b735aae-c39d-3dca-a040-0759bc7bb2aa", "product": {"name": "cilium"}, "product_version": "1.14.0, < 1.14.8"}, {"id": "7a3b133c-46b7-3afd-b159-3c0d169a4cb0", "product": {"name": "cilium"}, "product_version": "< 1.13.13"}, {"id": "9d3ff8d5-3967-3276-8819-0308339f64c9", "product": {"name": "cilium"}, "product_version": "1.15.0, < 1.15.2"}, {"id": "e6c9b7a1-a35b-3448-90c6-a27a530a133d", "product": {"name": "cilium"}}], "enisaIdVendor": [{"id": "e6c9b7a1-a35b-3448-90c6-a27a530a133d", "vendor": {"name": "cilium"}}], "isExploited": false}